@Microsoft:- Microsoft actively supports employee well-being by offering various perks, including access to snacks and designated break times. 
üç™ Snack Break Initiatives
In 2022, Microsoft 365 partnered with OREO THINS to launch the "THINVITE" initiative during National Cookie Month.  This program encouraged employees to take 15-minute snack breaks, which were scheduled directly into their calendars.  Participants received a limited-edition OREO THINS Snack Break Expansion Cookie Pack, featuring cookies with office tips from the iconic Microsoft assistant, Clippy, and a special accessory called the "Clippy Dippy" to aid in dunking cookies without mess.  Additionally, the initiative included a Microsoft Teams live event link to a playful video titled "Return to Pawfice," showcasing eight puppies in an office setting, aiming to provide a light-hearted break during the workday .
